# Review Contract

This file is the project-specific source of truth for evidence-based code review.

## Review scope

- Default: current task diff and directly affected contracts.
- Expanded scope: TBD
- Out of scope: TBD

## Reviewer separation and model policy

- Primary implementer/fixer: Claude Code.
- Independent reviewer: Codex CLI in read-only mode.
- Model policy: resolve the latest currently approved Codex model from authoritative current evidence immediately before each review; pass the exact model ID explicitly and record it with the review artifact.
- No silent fallback: if model resolution or Codex execution cannot be verified, mark the review `BLOCKED` or `PARTIALLY VERIFIED` rather than substituting Claude self-review.
- Re-review: required after every R0/R1 fix and changes affecting security, data, auth, money, migrations, or external contracts.

